<p><i><b>Confessions of an Economic Hit Man</b></i> (<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0452287081" class="internal">ISBN 0-452-28708-1</a>) is a book written by <a href="/wiki/John_Perkins_(author)" title="John Perkins (author)">John Perkins</a> and published in 2004. It provides Perkins' account of his career with consulting firm <a href="/wiki/Chas._T._Main" title="Chas. T. Main">Chas. T. Main</a>. Before employment with the firm, he interviewed for a job with the <a href="/wiki/National_Security_Agency" title="National Security Agency">National Security Agency</a> (NSA). Perkins claims that this interview effectively constituted an independent screening which led to his subsequent hiring by Einar Greve, a member of the firm (and alleged NSA liaison) to become a self-described "economic hit man".</p>
<p>John Perkins and his role as Economic Hitman (EHM) is one of the main themes in <a href="/wiki/Zeitgeist:_Addendum" title="Zeitgeist: Addendum" class="mw-redirect">part II of the movie Zeitgeist</a>, released October 2008.</p>
